snippet: Mulliken was a little-known college swimmer when he outpaced the world-record holder in the 200-meter breaststroke in the 1960 Summer Games.
abstract: Bill Mulliken, who won Olympic gold in 200-meter breaststroke in 1960 Games, dies at age 74.
lead_paragraph: Mulliken was a little-known college swimmer when he outpaced the world-record holder in the 200-meter breaststroke in the 1960 Summer Games.

headline.main: Bill Mulliken, Who Swam to Olympic Gold in 1960, Dies at 74
